  "text": "The industry has been subject to much public concern and scrutiny about practices within its supply base, probably more than most industries (de Brito et al 2008) . These have focused on employment practices, wages and working conditions, and the negative effects on the environment. More positively, the industry has been viewed by many of the less developed countries as an important source of employment for unskilled and semi-skilled labor and an important stepping stone for industrial development [CITATION_1] . Consequently, issues around the sustainability of clothing supply networks are highly relevant.",
